WEBVTT

00:00.767 --> 00:03.035
(OPENING THEME PLAYING)

00:21.054 --> 00:23.322
(FLUTE PLAYING)

00:24.257 --> 00:25.290
(GROWLING)

00:25.292 --> 00:26.391
The dragon!

00:26.393 --> 00:28.193
(ROARING)

00:28.195 --> 00:29.494
What's the plan, bro?

00:29.496 --> 00:31.530
There can only be one plan.

00:31.532 --> 00:34.333
I wanna ride that dragon!

00:34.335 --> 00:37.436
Oh, sick!
Ride that dragon, yo!

00:37.438 --> 00:41.073
Oh! I am riding this dragon!

00:41.075 --> 00:42.841
I too wish to ride the dragon!

00:42.843 --> 00:44.609
Then come ride
the dragon, girl!

00:44.611 --> 00:46.678
Now I am riding the dragon.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.613
Now she's riding the dragon.

00:48.615 --> 00:50.482
You two! Come up here
and ride this dragon!

00:50.484 --> 00:51.817
(SNAPS FINGERS)

00:51.819 --> 00:55.020
<i>♪ We're gonna ride that dragon</i>
<i>that dragon</i>

00:55.022 --> 00:58.824
<i>♪ We're gonna ride that dragon</i>
<i>that dragon</i>

00:58.826 --> 01:01.793
<i>♪ We're gonna ride that dragon</i>
<i>that dragon ♪</i>

01:01.795 --> 01:03.929
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
What is going on here?

01:03.931 --> 01:07.132
We're playing this
awesome game
called Dragon's Fire.

01:08.968 --> 01:11.436
It's really cool.
We pretend to ride a dragon.

01:11.438 --> 01:13.905
You should ride
the dragon with us!

01:13.907 --> 01:15.474
Oh, I'd love to.

01:15.476 --> 01:17.843
Except you're playing it
completely wrong!

01:17.845 --> 01:21.680
This game has
a strict set of rules
that must be followed.

01:21.682 --> 01:23.648
We don't care
about rules, bro.

01:23.650 --> 01:26.918
We just want
to get lost in the magic
of a fantasy world, yo.

01:26.920 --> 01:31.990
But if you follow the rules,
you'll experience a magical,
fantastical adventure

01:31.992 --> 01:34.192
that will leave you
frothing with joy!

01:34.194 --> 01:36.928
I wish to do the joy froth!

01:36.930 --> 01:38.063
(GULPING)

01:38.065 --> 01:39.731
Let's get magical, bro!

01:39.733 --> 01:43.602
All right! The first step
on your magical adventure

01:43.604 --> 01:45.237
is to fill these out.

01:45.239 --> 01:46.705
What is this, homework?

01:46.707 --> 01:49.241
Homework?
(BUZZER) Boring!

01:49.243 --> 01:52.077
This is a worksheet
to calculate
your character's skills

01:52.079 --> 01:53.845
using basic mathematics.

01:53.847 --> 01:56.681
Man, come on,
you know our brains
can't do math magics.

01:56.683 --> 01:58.150
(GROANS)

01:58.152 --> 02:00.051
Then just draw a picture
of your character
and I'll do the rest.

02:00.053 --> 02:01.119
That we can do.

02:01.121 --> 02:03.989
BEAST BOY:
<i>Check it. I'm a hyena!</i>

02:03.991 --> 02:05.424
(LAUGHING)

02:05.426 --> 02:07.759
RAVEN: <i> I'm a horrible monster</i>
<i>hiding under a cloak.</i>

02:07.761 --> 02:08.927
(ROARS)

02:08.929 --> 02:10.695
STARFIRE: <i> I am</i>
<i>the warrior princess!</i>

02:10.697 --> 02:13.165
CYBORG: <i> I'm a tinman, baby!</i>
<i>Clankity clank!</i>

02:13.167 --> 02:15.100
And your character, Robin?

02:15.102 --> 02:19.504
Oh, me? No big deal.
Just a half elf battle mage
called Nightslasher.

02:19.506 --> 02:21.973
Savior of the nine
kingdoms of men,

02:21.975 --> 02:25.710
Nightslasher wields not only
the magical staff of Gamesh,

02:25.712 --> 02:27.846
but the secret flute
of Katang.

02:27.848 --> 02:29.815
You got a stick and a flute?

02:29.817 --> 02:31.183
Nice.

02:31.185 --> 02:34.019
Thank you. Now, I've crafted
a magical adventure for us

02:34.021 --> 02:36.721
that involves some
pretty exciting stuff.

02:36.723 --> 02:39.224
-Riding dragons?
-No.

02:39.226 --> 02:41.860
-Necromancers?
-Nope.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.195
The fairies?

02:43.197 --> 02:46.998
Even better, we will embark
upon a quest to retrieve

02:47.000 --> 02:48.266
a key.

02:48.268 --> 02:49.534
A magical key?

02:49.536 --> 02:50.769
ROBIN: A regular key!

02:50.771 --> 02:52.270
That opens a magic door?

02:52.272 --> 02:54.039
A regular door!

02:54.041 --> 02:55.073
That sounds boring.

02:55.075 --> 02:57.409
I knew you'd be excited!
Let's get started.

02:57.411 --> 03:01.246
Our party travels upon
the southern road
towards Th'lach'mo'or

03:01.248 --> 03:04.416
through the ancient forest
of Threllegh'vehn!

03:04.418 --> 03:06.685
-Thrella what?
-Threllegh'vehn!

03:06.687 --> 03:08.220
Trailing vahagaha?

03:08.222 --> 03:10.922
The forest! Your party
is in the forest.

03:10.924 --> 03:14.159
Forest, huh?
I wanna climb some trees!

03:14.161 --> 03:15.494
Okay, roll the dice.

03:15.496 --> 03:19.097
No, bro, I said
I want to climb trees.

03:19.099 --> 03:22.100
In this game, these dice
determine your every action!

03:22.102 --> 03:24.903
If you want to climb a tree,
you have to roll the dice.

03:24.905 --> 03:26.705
Ugh. Fine.

03:26.707 --> 03:30.876
A one! Yeah! I'm number one!
That's good, right?

03:30.878 --> 03:33.512
Ooh. No.
That is the worst number.

03:33.514 --> 03:37.249
Hyena falls from the tree,
hits his head on a branch
and gets a concussion.

03:37.251 --> 03:38.483
Oh, come on!

03:38.485 --> 03:40.185
I wish to search
for the fairies!

03:40.187 --> 03:43.989
Ooh. The warrior princess
attempts to search for fairies

03:43.991 --> 03:45.957
but hits her head on a branch
and gets a concussion.

03:45.959 --> 03:47.025
Sadness.

03:47.027 --> 03:49.194
-Yeah, this is boring.
-It's magical!

03:49.196 --> 03:51.897
Then why do you keep
killing the magic
with all this boring stuff?

03:51.899 --> 03:55.133
I told you, the game
has a strict set of rules!

03:55.135 --> 03:57.269
-Forget that.
-I'm gonna find a dragon.

03:58.938 --> 04:00.572
-There he is!
-(ROARING)

04:00.574 --> 04:03.341
No! There is not!
I told you to play
by the rules!

04:03.343 --> 04:04.476
You're ruining everything!

04:04.478 --> 04:05.644
(WHIRRING)

04:05.646 --> 04:07.779
-(ALL GASPING)
-What is the happening?

04:08.347 --> 04:09.881
(ALL SCREAMING)

04:14.253 --> 04:16.555
-Whoa!
-I look so cool!

04:16.557 --> 04:18.390
Oh, my! We have the epicness!

04:18.392 --> 04:20.392
Wow! We're super fresh!

04:20.394 --> 04:24.029
Hmm. I'd imagined I'd be
a little taller than this.

04:24.031 --> 04:27.198
I think we're in that forest
of Chillavagahanahaja.

04:28.067 --> 04:30.101
Threllegh'vhehn.

04:30.103 --> 04:31.970
Truluvuluhulahu.

04:31.972 --> 04:33.738
(ANGRILY) Threllegh'vhehn!

04:33.740 --> 04:35.774
-Threfelha.
-Troopadoopadoo.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.776
Just call it the forest!

04:37.778 --> 04:39.644
And obviously,
we're now stuck in here

04:39.646 --> 04:42.414
because you
didn't follow the rules
of the game.

04:42.416 --> 04:46.384
So, when you said
the game was magical,
you meant, like, for real?

04:46.386 --> 04:49.487
Of course. It's all about
wizards and dragons.
What did you expect?

04:49.489 --> 04:53.124
This is actually pretty cool.
We could see
a dragon for real.

04:53.126 --> 04:56.161
STARFIRE: (GASPS) <i> We could</i>
<i>ride the dragon for the reals!</i>

04:56.163 --> 04:57.929
Absolutely not.

04:57.931 --> 05:00.999
That's the kind
of imaginative excitement
that got us into this mess.

05:01.001 --> 05:05.070
The only way out
is to finish the original
adventure and find the key.

05:05.072 --> 05:08.106
We'll start where
all great adventures start.

05:08.108 --> 05:10.108
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

05:11.644 --> 05:14.779
CYBORG: What kind of
great adventure starts
at a greasy motel?

05:14.781 --> 05:16.281
ROBIN:
It's a charming inn!

05:16.283 --> 05:17.682
(DOOR CREAKING)

05:17.684 --> 05:19.784
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

05:21.654 --> 05:24.823
Good morrow,
m'lords and gentlefolk.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.192
(BURPS)

05:30.663 --> 05:33.131
Oh, look. A grizzled
old innkeeper like that

05:33.133 --> 05:35.400
is sure to point us
in the direction of adventure.

05:35.402 --> 05:36.835
(SPITS)

05:38.104 --> 05:39.604
Ew.

05:39.606 --> 05:44.576
Hark, innkeep, have you
any work for a band
of brave adventurers?

05:44.578 --> 05:45.944
I've got a problem.

05:45.946 --> 05:47.679
(SPITS)

05:47.681 --> 05:49.214
Vicious creatures
in the basement.

05:49.216 --> 05:53.318
Claws. Red eyes.
Fangs like you've never seen.

05:53.320 --> 05:54.486
Dragons?

05:54.488 --> 05:56.221
Rats. (SPITS)

05:57.323 --> 05:58.723
So? Call an exterminator.

05:58.725 --> 06:00.792
Now, let us find
the real adventure.

06:00.794 --> 06:04.696
Hey! Remember,
to get home we have to
finish this adventure.

06:04.698 --> 06:06.064
Fine.
(GROANS)

06:06.066 --> 06:08.033
But we want to see
something magical, bro.

06:08.035 --> 06:11.770
Oh, you'll see something
magical all right.

06:12.405 --> 06:13.638
(DOOR CREAKS)

06:13.640 --> 06:15.040
(BLOWS)

06:16.776 --> 06:18.309
Steady yourselves.

06:18.311 --> 06:20.912
I've got this.
Rats are my bros.

06:21.414 --> 06:22.480
(HISSING)

06:22.482 --> 06:23.615
Ahhh!

06:23.617 --> 06:24.916
They're not bros!

06:24.918 --> 06:26.885
I told you we'd see
something magical.

06:26.887 --> 06:29.287
Look at the size
of those rats!

06:29.289 --> 06:30.555
To arms, friends!

06:30.557 --> 06:34.492
Prepare to taste
the Tinman's warhammer.
(ROARING)

06:34.494 --> 06:36.528
(METAL CREAKING)

06:36.530 --> 06:38.263
I can't attack 'em.

06:38.265 --> 06:39.764
Of course you can't.
You have to roll
the dice to attack.

06:39.766 --> 06:42.033
Really?
(GROANS)

06:42.035 --> 06:44.502
Another one?
This dice is broken.

06:44.504 --> 06:46.104
Now, the rats get to roll.

06:47.373 --> 06:49.908
A 10. Not bad.

06:49.910 --> 06:53.078
(CYBORG SCREAMING)

06:54.346 --> 06:56.181
Give me that.

06:56.183 --> 06:59.718
Nice. Azarath Metrion Zinthos!

07:01.220 --> 07:02.554
Phew.

07:02.556 --> 07:04.089
(SCREAMING)

07:04.091 --> 07:06.191
Did Raven not cast her spell?

07:06.193 --> 07:10.428
Yes. And it worked.
Didn't you see how the rats
were distracted for a moment?

07:10.430 --> 07:12.430
I cast a distraction spell?

07:12.432 --> 07:15.400
You're only level one.
So, well, that's
your best spell.

07:15.402 --> 07:17.902
Now your rules are taking
the magic out of magic!

07:17.904 --> 07:20.939
(SCREAMING) Ow!
Make them stop!

07:22.274 --> 07:23.742
Give me that!

07:25.344 --> 07:26.845
Azarath Metrion Zinthos!

07:26.847 --> 07:28.313
(BLASTING)

07:29.215 --> 07:30.615
(BONES CLANKING)

07:30.617 --> 07:33.284
(GROANING)
That was against
the rules of the game!

07:33.286 --> 07:34.819
And yet it worked.

07:34.821 --> 07:37.122
I can't believe this.
People making up rules,
messing up everything.

07:37.124 --> 07:41.526
Ooh! Look! There appears
to be a secret passage
from where the rats came.

07:41.528 --> 07:44.596
Exciting! You guys feeling it?
The adventure?

07:44.598 --> 07:45.930
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

07:45.932 --> 07:47.499
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

07:47.501 --> 07:51.369
<i>♪ A necromancer</i>
<i>we're under his spell</i>

07:52.805 --> 07:56.207
<i>♪ Crossing a bridge</i>
<i>where the goblins dwell</i>

07:58.043 --> 08:01.479
<i>♪ Skeleton dudes</i>
<i>that will make you scream</i>

08:02.848 --> 08:05.984
<i>♪ Nothing in here's</i>
<i>quite what it seems</i>

08:08.120 --> 08:10.288
<i>♪ Down in the dungeon</i>

08:10.290 --> 08:13.057
<i>♪ Gotta find the key</i>
<i>find the key</i>

08:13.059 --> 08:15.193
<i>♪ Down in the dungeon</i>

08:15.195 --> 08:18.129
<i>♪ Gotta find the key</i>
<i>find the key ♪</i>

08:22.835 --> 08:25.003
Ready yourselves.
(INHALES)

08:25.005 --> 08:28.540
Who knows what awaits us
beyond this door.

08:28.542 --> 08:31.476
(GASPS)
Perhaps it is the fairy party!

08:31.478 --> 08:35.246
Oh, sick! All dancing
with mermaids
and jellyfish massages...

08:35.248 --> 08:40.952
Stop imagining things!
Mermaids and fairies are not
going to help us find the key!

08:40.954 --> 08:43.188
Now, stand ready.

08:43.756 --> 08:46.257
ALL: A dragon!

08:46.259 --> 08:47.625
(SHUSHING)

08:47.627 --> 08:50.228
(WHISPERING)
If this dragon wakes up,
it will eat our heads.

08:50.230 --> 08:55.733
Now, follow me. They key
to getting us out of here
is within our sight.

08:55.735 --> 08:57.035
We're almost clear.

08:57.037 --> 08:58.102
What are you doing?

08:58.104 --> 08:59.904
We wanna ride the dragon!

08:59.906 --> 09:01.873
Just for one tiny minute.

09:01.875 --> 09:03.775
Absolutely not!

09:03.777 --> 09:05.443
Bro, that is a straight-up
dragon that we could
be riding right now.

09:05.445 --> 09:07.679
Yeah. You said this world
was full of magic,

09:07.681 --> 09:10.515
but we ain't done nothing
but roll dices and fight rats!

09:10.517 --> 09:13.952
That's the game!
And we could be doing that
from the comfort of our couch.

09:13.954 --> 09:19.123
But no, you had to use
your dumb imaginations
and look where that got us!

09:19.125 --> 09:20.191
(SLAMS)

09:22.194 --> 09:23.461
Ooh.

09:26.065 --> 09:29.667
You blame them
for being trapped here?

09:29.669 --> 09:31.936
Um, yes. They broke the rules.

09:31.938 --> 09:33.471
(LAUGHING)

09:33.473 --> 09:36.641
-Young elf, it was
you who caused this.
-What?

09:36.643 --> 09:40.245
You were brought here
for ruining this magical game.

09:40.247 --> 09:41.779
(LAUGHING)

09:41.781 --> 09:43.081
Oh, in the face.

09:43.083 --> 09:45.049
Imagination is true magic.

09:45.051 --> 09:49.621
It has no rules.
It's so simple, I can't
believe you didn't know that.

09:49.623 --> 09:51.522
(LAUGHING)

09:51.524 --> 09:53.057
I wanna ride that dragon!

09:53.059 --> 09:54.292
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

09:54.294 --> 09:56.094
Come ride the dragon
with us, bro!

09:56.096 --> 10:00.265
Yes, young elf,
come and ride me!

10:00.267 --> 10:03.234
Well, I guess I could
give it a try.

10:04.904 --> 10:07.972
I'm riding the dragon!
And it's fun!

10:07.974 --> 10:10.441
<i>♪ We're gonna ride the dragon</i>

10:10.443 --> 10:11.376
<i>♪ The dragon</i>

10:11.378 --> 10:13.778
<i>♪ We're gonna ride the dragon</i>

10:13.780 --> 10:14.979
<i>♪ The dragon</i>

10:14.981 --> 10:16.748
<i>♪ We're gonna ride the dragon</i>

10:16.750 --> 10:18.216
<i>♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

10:18.218 --> 10:20.151
<i>♪ The dragon</i>
<i>we're gonna ride the dragon ♪</i>

10:20.153 --> 10:24.856
Delightful. Delightful.
This is true magic
and fantasy.

10:24.858 --> 10:28.126
Congratulations.
(LAUGHING)

10:28.827 --> 10:30.895
And now, you fry.

10:30.897 --> 10:32.363
ALL: What?

10:32.365 --> 10:34.232
(FIRE ROARING)
